<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4653303-kara-rutledge"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1303676739i/4653303._UX100_CR0,9,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4653303-kara-rutledge">Kara Rutledge</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Most of them are really good and age appropriate . . . The Doll in the Garden, Time of the Witch, The Jellyfish Season, Stepping on the Cracks, The De<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Most of them are really good and age appropriate . . . The Doll in the Garden, Time of the Witch, The Jellyfish Season, Stepping on the Cracks, The Dead Man in Indian Creek, and The Spanish Kidnapping Disaster were my go to books by Mary Downing Hahn when I was 11. December Stillness was good for kids a little older.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
