    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3861185333" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3861185333" />
    <a title="Cameron Chaney" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40648249-cameron-chaney"><img alt="Cameron Chaney" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1596633386p2/40648249.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3861185333?book_show_action=true">Feb 26, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cameron Chaney" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cameron Chaney" href="/user/show/40648249-cameron-chaney">Cameron Chaney</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40648249-cameron-chaney?shelf=spooky">spooky</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40648249-cameron-chaney?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40648249-cameron-chaney?shelf=middle-grade">middle-grade</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40648249-cameron-chaney?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3861185333" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15320258047963012664">I recently read <i>One for Sorrow</i> by Mary Downing Hahn and thought it was a decent ghost story for middle grade readers, but it made me nostalgic for Hahn&apos;s older work. I read <i>Wait Till Helen Comes</i> way back in sixth grade. I remembered loving it and always categorized it as a favorite, so I figured it was the perfect book to revisit, especially in February during women of horror month. Happily, this was just as good as I remembered it being. So much nostalgia! It&apos;s creepy, dark (for a children&apos;s bo</span>
  <span id="freeText15320258047963012664" style="display:none">I recently read <i>One for Sorrow</i> by Mary Downing Hahn and thought it was a decent ghost story for middle grade readers, but it made me nostalgic for Hahn's older work. I read <i>Wait Till Helen Comes</i> way back in sixth grade. I remembered loving it and always categorized it as a favorite, so I figured it was the perfect book to revisit, especially in February during women of horror month. Happily, this was just as good as I remembered it being. So much nostalgia! It's creepy, dark (for a children's book), masterfully paced, cozy, and gothic, but it's also a great summer read. The descriptions of warm nights and green fields glowing with fireflies made my heart long for those bright, sunny months even more.<br /><br />Yep, this one is still a favorite! <b>5 stars.</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="15320258047963012664" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

