<span id="freeTextContainer2739125876633373983">This was a *re-read* of one of my favorites as a kid. (One of my own kids is writing a book report on it, so I thought I&apos;d pick it up to refresh my memory). I have to say, as an adult, I found a lot &quot;wrong&quot; with this book, but as a kid, it seemed perfectly natural for parents to say, &quot;Go play&quot; in a strange neighborhood, and not see their kids again until dinner time.... ;)<br/><br/>Three stars, as an adult.</span>
  <span id="freeText2739125876633373983" style="display:none">This was a *re-read* of one of my favorites as a kid. (One of my own kids is writing a book report on it, so I thought I'd pick it up to refresh my memory). I have to say, as an adult, I found a lot "wrong" with this book, but as a kid, it seemed perfectly natural for parents to say, "Go play" in a strange neighborhood, and not see their kids again until dinner time.... ;)<br /><br />Three stars, as an adult.</span>
